<br>
So what's left for me to do at this point...<br>
<br>
Quests?  Ride a horse, talk to npc, ride a horse, talk to npc, ride horse, kill mob, ride horse, talk to npc, get item.  5 hours afk on a horse, 2 minutes fighting, not fun.  Additionally, no high level quests exist besides &quot;Class Epics&quot;.<br>
<br>
Tradeskills?  Player-made goods, billed as the best available in game, have been made completely obsolete by mob drops.<br>
<br>
Item Farming?  Non-existant.  At least half of the zones are unitemized.  Many items are overly rare and/or placed on the wrong mobs.  Example 1:  The best bracers I can wear drop from from grey mobs (L28), and they drop 1 in 20,000 kills.  So few exist that they cannot be bought at any price, and I can no longer get them myself.  Example 2:  Level 14 Ring of Arwan dropping off Level 45 Cyclops.<br>
<br>
PvP?  aka Farming realm points that serve no immediate purpose.  No thanks.  I play an overpowered class.  I'm Rank 4.  I have nothing to show for it.  I might have some Legend of Zelda-esqe health potions soon.<br>
<br>
PvP isn't fun.  It's a series of 5-30 second battles.  When everyone is killed in 1-5 hits by someone their level, there isn't much skill involved and there's not alot of tactics used.  Occasionally 1v1 or 2v2 fights are interesting, and fun, but these are basically non-existant.<br>
<br>
RvR?  Keeps and Relics are a waste of time.  If they were meaningful, there'd almost be some initative to level, defend your realm, and conquor your enemies.  We assumed it would be this way when we started playing, but it's obviously not.  &quot;Realm Pride&quot; is the only thing that keeps us defending, when there should be something tangible worth fighting for.<br>
<br>
Whine on &quot;The Vault&quot; Boards?<br>
<br>
Quit?<br>
<br>
eBay?<br>
<br>
I'm running out of options.  I'll give em a couple months to sort this out before I'm gone.<br>
<br>
&quot;Syrrok&quot;<br>
IceClan<br>
Scout<br>
